ZH: 1. 他们的亲密关系被一场意外拆散了。
EN: 1. Their close relationship was broken apart by an accident.
ZH: 2. 我将努力不拆散这个家庭。
EN: 2. I will try my best not to break apart this family.
ZH: 3. 这场争吵几乎拆散了他们的友谊。
EN: 3. The argument almost tore their friendship apart.
ZH: 4. 他并没有拆散他们，只是提出一个不同的观点。
EN: 4. He didn't break them apart, he just proposed a different viewpoint.
ZH: 5. 他曾经是那个家庭的纽带，但现在却成了拆散者。
EN: 5. He used to be the bond of that family, but now he has become the one who breaks them apart.
ZH: 6. 这个新闻可能会拆散两位有望合作的明星。
EN: 6. This news might break apart the promising collaboration between two celebrities.
ZH: 7. 他是个搅屎棍，专门拆散别人的幸福。
EN: 7. He is a troublemaker who deliberately breaks apart others' happiness.
ZH: 8. 谣言和八卦常常会拆散人们之间的信任。
EN: 8. Rumors and gossip often break apart trust between people.
ZH: 9. 她不愿意拆散任何人的家庭。
EN: 9. She doesn't want to break apart anyone's family.
ZH: 10. 倔强的个性导致他拆散了与他人的合作机会。
EN: 10. His stubbornness led him to break apart opportunities to cooperate with others.
ZH: 11. 他最终拆散了他们的友谊纽带，因为他缺乏信任。
EN: 11. He eventually broke apart their bond of friendship because of his lack of trust.
ZH: 12. 那个阴险的计划几乎拆散了他们的团队。
EN: 12. The cunning plan almost tore their team apart.
ZH: 13. 她的离去确实拆散了我们的心。
EN: 13. Her departure did indeed break apart our hearts.
ZH: 14. 他早就感到他们之间的友情即将被拆散。
EN: 14. He had already sensed that the friendship between them was about to be broken apart.
ZH: 15. 负面的讨论会拆散整个团体的合作精神。
EN: 15. Negative discussions can break apart the spirit of collaboration within the whole group.
ZH: 16. 老师严厉地警告我们，不要做任何会拆散班级团结的事情。
EN: 16. The teacher sternly warned us not to do anything that would break apart the unity of the class.
ZH: 17. 他的谎言最终拆散了他与家人的关系。
EN: 17. His lies ultimately broke apart his relationship with his family.
ZH: 18. 那场争吵拆散了他们原本亲密的友谊。
EN: 18. That argument broke apart their once close friendship.
ZH: 19. 寻找我们共同的利益可以避免拆散我们之间的合作。
EN: 19. Seeking our common interests can avoid breaking apart our collaboration.
ZH: 20. 可悲的是，这场意外拆散了他们的美好爱情。
EN: 20. Sadly, this accident broke apart their beautiful love.
